-- GE restructures into four business segments
-- 
-- Fri Jul 25, 2008 3:13pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/07/25/us-ge-structure-idUSWNAB281620080725

 

 BOSTON  (Reuters) - General Electric Co ( GE.N ) announced a restructuring of its organization on Friday making its energy-related units into their own branch of the second-largest U.S. company by market capitalization. 

 The new structure of four units, down from six, is: GE Technology Infrastructure, which will now include GE Health Care, as well as its aviation and transportation businesses; GE Energy Infrastructure; GE Capital, encompassing both commercial and consumer finance, and NBC Universal. John Krenicki, the head of GE's energy unit, has been named a vice chairman of the company, GE said. (Reporting by  Scott Malone , editing by Leslie Gevirtz)